Compared to most countries living in the USA is like living in a perpetual Disneyland.  Having inherited so much from the generations that came before us I believe that as a nation we should give a helping hand to anyone that is willing to work hard to build their future, like our parents and grandparents did but on a global scale.  

And the most important reason I lend is because my spirit guide told me it was good karma and will help me balance out a lifetime of drunkenness, sloth, debauchery, greed and self indulgence.  Man, I'm going to have to make a lot of loans!
lenders.occupational_info:
I have two cats. The older of the two I originally named Al-Qaeda because when she came into my life she was feral and didn't do much other than bite and scratch and hiss if you tried to pick her up.  There were times when I though she had been taught on the mean streets of Southeast Texas to  be a mob enforcer or possibly a suicide bomber for some radical fundamentalist cat religion.  My father who passed a couple years ago spent hundreds and hundreds of hours patiently giving her a lot of love and over several years her demeanor became much more feminine and gentle.  I've heard thad dogs have masters, cats have servents. Now that Ive become this biting scratching hissing fuzzball with sharp claws servant I've discovered the name Al-Qaeda really doesn't fit anymore as she has changed so much.  Her time with my dad changed and formed her in profound ways. The same happened with me, and for that I will be eternally grateful.  Anyway enough about cats...
I think mean people suck. I voted for Obama.  I'm still not sure if that was the right decision but at least he's not a Republican.
As for my spiritual life, I find I need one and it must be cultivated at least from time to time.  Since 2008 I have been attending a Buddhist Temple for meditation and Dhama talks.  Buddhism requires no faith in any what I call Hocus Pocus like walking on water or turning water into wine.  Rather to practice Buddhism (which is a philosophy not a religion) you must accept ideas NOT ON FAITH, but by practical observation of ones actions and outcomes.  Before his death Joseph Campbell, well known author and scholar  who spent his entire career studying in great detail the world  religions and publishing books and articles on his research made mention that if he had to choose a religion it would be Buddhism.  To my knowledge he never claimed to be anything other than an athiest and a researcher. 
I'm single, 46 years old, disease free, own my own home, and am hoping to find some rich drop dead georgous older woman who loves kinky sex to spend my time with.  The  rich part is optional, as is the age part. 
I just made my first loan tonight.  I hope to meet some kewl interesting people on here as a side benefit to helping others.
